    "liner_notes": "Recorded over three days in August 1969, *Bitches Brew* is the sound of Miles Davis dismantling the future and reassembling it with electric instruments and studio tape manipulation. Producer Teo Macero's editing — splicing, looping, overdubbing — created a new kind of sonic architecture. The album launched the careers of Wayne Shorter, Chick Corea, John McLaughlin, and Herbie Hancock, who were all transformed by the experience.",
